  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China launches Yaogan-33 2 satellite",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The China Yaogan-33 02 satellite was launched aboard a Long March 4C carrier rocket on Saturday from the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in northwest China at 11:00 a.m. Beijing time. Launched at 7:44 p.m.",
        "Accordingly, China says that the satellite entered its preset orbit, signaling that the launch was a complete success.",
        "It is used for scientific experiments, national land resources census, yield estimation of agricultural products and disaster prevention.",
        "The launch marked the 435th flight of the Long March series of launch vehicles."
      ],
